HEADWORD: Harness cask
<hw>Har"ness cask`</hw> <pr>(k⟦adot⟧sk`)</pr>. <fld>(Naut.)</fld> <def>A
tub lashed to a vessel's deck and containing salted provisions for daily
use; -- called also <altname>harness tub</altname>.</def> <rj><au>W. C.
Russell.</au></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Harnesser</ent>⟦br⟧
